# Code of Conduct

We are committed to providing a friendly, safe and welcoming environment for all, regardless of gender, sexual orientation, disability, ethnicity, religion, or similar personal characteristic.

By participating in this project, you agree to uphold our code of conduct.

## Expected Behavior

- Be respectful and considerate towards others
- Communicate with courtesy and professionalism
- Listen actively and be open to differing viewpoints
- Accept constructive criticism and feedback gracefully

## Unacceptable Behavior

- Harassment, intimidation, or discrimination of any kind
- Offensive or derogatory comments, gestures or images
- Personal attacks or trolling
- Inappropriate or unwelcome advances
- Any other conduct which could reasonably be considered inappropriate in a professional setting

## Consequences of Unacceptable Behavior

We take our code of conduct seriously and will not tolerate any behavior that goes against it. If you engage in any unacceptable behavior, we may take any appropriate action, including, but not limited to:

- Issuing a verbal warning
- Asking you to leave the discussion or event
- Temporarily or permanently banning you from participating in the project

## Reporting Guidelines

If you witness or experience any behavior that violates our code of conduct, please report it immediately to [insert contact information here]. We will investigate and take appropriate action.

## Attribution

This code of conduct is adapted from the Contributor Covenant (http://contributor-covenant.org), version 1.4, available at https://www.contributor-covenant.org/version/1/4/code-of-conduct.html.
